<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
This apparently sterile hybrid differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Bieb., Fl. Taur. - Caucas. 1: 147. 1808. (Marschall von Bieberstein" authorityYear="1808" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus holosericeus" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holosericeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Convolvulus holosericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of pouched sepals and differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stace, Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 64: 58. 1971. (Stace" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="compactus">Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus</taxonomicName>
in the adpressed sericeous indumentum and in the stigma that is distinctly shorter than (rather than about equalling) the style.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distribution.</paragraph>
